➜British diplomat awarded special award for saving girl in water
http://www.sohu.com/a/433947359_162758	22995
<p>Recently, a video entitled "foreign elderly rescue drowning girls in Chongqing" has attracted attention on the Internet. On the morning of November 14, 61 year old British Consul General in Chongqing was visiting Zhongshan ancient town in Chongqing when he suddenly heard the cry of the crowd and found a young girl falling into the water. Shi yunsen immediately jumped into the water and lifted the unconscious girl out of the water. With the help of rescue personnel on the shore, he safely sent the girl to the shore. As a result of timely rescue, the girl quickly recovered breathing and consciousness, no major obstacle.</p>
<p>Liu Xiaoming, Chinese ambassador to the UK, immediately praised Mr. Shi yunsen on social media. Ambassador Liu wrote that he paid tribute to the new British Consul General in Chongqing. His name will be remembered not only in Chongqing, but also in China. His heroic deeds will be a good story of Sino British friendship.</p>
<p><img src="http://p7.itc.cn/q_70/images03/20201124/59cc85e2abaa4f148bf7857fac7df82f.png" /></p>
<p>Chinese ambassador to the UK Liu Xiaoming praised consul general Shi yunsen's heroic deeds on social media.</p>
<p>A British diplomat has been hailed as a hero after diving into a river in China and rescuing a drowning student, the BBC website said on November 16.</p>            <div class="lookall-box">
<div class="lookall-shadow"></div>
<section class="lookall">
<a href="javascript:;" class="show-all" id="showMore">
<em>展开全文</em>
</a>
</section>
</div>
<div class="hidden-content control-hide">
<p>Stephen Ellison, 61, the British Consul General in Chongqing, was walking by the river in a nearby town when he came across an accident. A young woman walked to the edge of a river beach to take a picture, but she slipped and fell into the river.</p>
<p>The video taken by passers-by showed that the woman was struggling in the turbulent current and was about to disappear under the stone bridge, face down, and was obviously unconscious.</p>
<p>Seeing this, he immediately took off his shoes and jumped into the water to save people. Swanson, who had participated in the triathlon, turned the girl over, lifted her head out of the water and swam backward to the steep bank.</p>
<p>"She lost consciousness, she didn't breathe, and for a while we were worried about the worst. But when we got back to the shore, she began to breathe again</p>
<p>Finally, with the help of all, Swanson grabbed the life buoy attached to the rope thrown to him by passers-by and landed safely with the drowning man. Both of them were in good health. After Swanson came ashore, "he was taken good care of by the local villagers" and brought him hot coffee and dry clothes to change.</p>
<p><img src="http://p9.itc.cn/q_70/images03/20201124/ab241a487d914cf6aa730622b71ca120.png" /></p>
<p>Screenshot of BBC report</p>
<p>Shi yunsen said the student from Wuhan and studying at Chongqing University is slowly recovering. She was very grateful to swinson and invited him to dinner with her family next weekend.</p>
<p>On the Chinese Internet, Shi yunsen's kindness to save people is highly praised. Social media users call him a "hero" and "model", and a "admirable" person.</p>
<p>"In England, you call him a knight; in China, we call him a hero." One Sina Weibo user wrote.</p>
<p>Another netizen wrote, "this is the same as my feeling when I came to the UK. No matter what difficulties you encounter, the British people around you will always come to help you when they see you need help. This is really warm to me!"!!! I hope everything is well. "</p>
<p><img src="http://p1.itc.cn/q_70/images03/20201124/9ee063c1578d4d9eba9fd36c80485b9d.png" /></p>
<p>Screenshot of ITV's website</p>
<p>ITV interviewed Swanson's 83 year old mother, Annabel Ellison. His 61 year old son seems to be the brave boy in his mother's eyes. She said she was proud of her son and would be "extremely proud" if her late husband were here today.</p>
<p><img src="http://p4.itc.cn/q_70/images03/20201124/eef8d49da59e43518a273030ffac0abf.png" /></p>
<p>Swinson's 83 year old mother, Annabel, wept with pride at her son's kindness.</p>
<p>Swinson told reporters that it was "nothing special" and he just did the right thing. "I didn't think too much, just jumped into the water, hoping to help No thinking, just trying to do the right thing, trying to help others.</p>
<p><img src="http://p6.itc.cn/q_70/images03/20201124/49cea0a3c3a3448cb069f513fa24db41.png" /></p>
<p>At the end of the interview, swinson also showed the British cold humor. People keep asking him if he is cold But "they forget I'm from Newcastle."</p>
<p>On the 20th, the reporter learned from the Chongqing foundation for good Samaritan that Mr. Shi yunsen's act of giving up his own life to save others has been widely concerned and praised by the society and the media. In order to commend Mr. Shi's brave deeds, the Chongqing foundation for good Samaritan decided to award Mr. Shi yunsen the "Chongqing Special Award for righteous deeds" and reward RMB 50000.</p>
